content: Painfully going through it for how boring and uninteresting it is. A failed attempt at being deep and delivering an observation. Don't recommend waisting a second on it. Also it is not a game if you are looking for one. It is an interactive piece but no game in there.

You would get the same amount of interaction in my opinion.

Excellent experience but too short. I wish it had a more fleshed out, longer experience that amounted to a story but it was very creative and executed well. i suggest expanding on the concept and building a story out of it. I look forward to an update.

It's one-step-from-minimalist modern art that takes 15-20 minutes of your attention to present each of a handful of thoughts over and over again. As art does work but it feels like it demands a lot of investment for how shallow the thoughts it gives actually are.
This is what I'd call an art game. The gameplay isn't great, but it is an interesting experience. I doubt I'll play it through a second time.
There's a metaphor in here somewhere. Not 100% sure what it is, but I think it's super meaningful? 5 stars.
Charming and stylish, weird little game with no clear plot, goals or dialogue, more like a sequence of different abstract interactions in which you tweak stuff to figure out a way to proceed.
If there is supposed to be a deeper meaning I have to confess I don't get it. It's... weird. I'm not sure I like it and I have to wonder if that's intentional.
